## Comparative Overview of Key Strategies

| Strategy                          | Description                                      | Impact on Deforestation                         | Challenges                                  |
|----------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------|
| Tree Planting & Reforestation    | Planting new trees to restore forests           | Directly increases forest cover, carbon sequestration | Requires long-term commitment and resources |
| Reducing Paper & Wood Use         | Paperless transactions, recycling, FSC products | Lowers demand for timber, reduces logging      | Requires behavioral change and infrastructure |
| Sustainable Agriculture          | Crop rotation, reduced meat consumption         | Limits forest clearing for farmland             | Economic and cultural barriers               |
| Legal Enforcement & Policies     | Laws banning illegal logging, incentives         | Deters illegal activities, promotes sustainable use | Enforcement difficulties, corruption        |
| Technological Innovations        | Blockchain, AI, mobile apps                       | Improves monitoring and transparency            | High initial costs, technology access        |
| Public Awareness & Education     | Campaigns, school programs                        | Changes consumer behavior and policy support    | Requires continuous effort                    |
| Indigenous Rights Support        | Land rights, partnerships                         | Proven effective in forest conservation         | Political resistance, land conflicts          |

